misc: Was discharged from the military, 1863-2-28, on account of lung disease contracted in service.  On 1864-4-18, began to study dentistry with Dr. C.R. Smith of Grayville IL.  In 1864-7, returned to his former regiment where his brother was in command; served in campaign through Shenandoah Valley, VA under General Sheridan; took part in the battles of Oppequan (or Winchester), 1864-9-19, Fisher's Hill, 1864-9-22, and Cedar Creek, 1864-10-19, assisting his brother in command.  In spring of 1865, resumed study of dentistry with Dr. Smith.  Began to practice dentistry in Grayville, 1881.  Was the first mayor of Grayville.
